pr_body:
1. Winner is clearly highlighted.
2. Case where more than one options is winner is handled (bars for multiple options appear in blue, when there's a clear winner - winner bar appears in blue, remaining appear in black)
3. Total votes displayed dynamically.
4. Final Results signalled when poll ends.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28918901/120818619-69627000-c570-11eb-8d50-a2e877766af9.mp4

Reference: https://www.figma.com/file/mDXZpw12HxPQhOkMQ9pBRj/Add-Emoticons

pr_body:
- IPoll interface's `confidential?: boolean` property updated to `visibility?: string`.
-  Added `anonymousOptions: Array<string>` property to IPoll interface.
- Mixed Visibility modal with MultiStaticSelectElement pops open when poll creator chooses "Mixed Visibility vote".
- Makes mixed visibility stay consistent on finishing poll and when users cast votes.
- Allows mixed visibility polls to be created within threads.
- Shows anonymous marked responses as voted by "Anonymous" user.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28918901/123508369-95af6f00-d68c-11eb-9e2b-afe63280a32b.mp4



Closes #4

We have other properties like `view.id` which we usually use to for this purpose. We append a constant string to the id like `create_poll_form-${ uuid() }` while creating the view and them over here in `executeViewSubmitHandler` we determine the modal action via the prefix we'd earlier attached", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 4, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673212232, 'comment_body': 'Why use the modify method to open a modal here when the context already provides an interface for sending a response modal. Checkout `context.getInteractionResponder().openModalViewResponse()`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 8, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 674235570, 'comment_body': "Using openModalViewResponse here doesn't actually open up the modal.
What's the difference between [openModalView](https://rocketchat.github.io/Rocket.Chat.Apps-engine/interfaces/accessors_iuicontroller.iuicontroller.html#openmodalview) and [openModalViewResponse](https://rocketchat.github.io/Rocket.Chat.Apps-engine/classes/uikit_uikitinteractionresponder.uikitinteractionresponder.html#openmodalviewresponse) ?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 21, 18, 38, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RonLek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 675972791, 'comment_body': "(Future Reference) Difference between `openModalView` and `openModalViewResponse`
The first renders a new modal from scratch, however the second only updates the modal components. On using `openModalViewResponse` the first modal sticks around even after submitting the second one (which we don't need for our current use-case).

Why not use `updateModalViewResponse()`?
The modal that's to be passed to it should have the same id as the one already opened (`create-poll-modal-uuid()`) for both create poll and mixed visibility modal).
This defeats the purpose - since we're trying to act based on the modal id (impossible to differentiate if they're the same) instead of the modal title. 

Therefore, decided to go ahead with `openModalView` using `modify`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 24, 9, 5, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RonLek', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: [NEW] Word cloud generation for poll responses
pr_body:
- `wordcloud` property added to IPoll interface.
- Used [Quickchart API](https://quickchart.io/documentation/word-cloud-api/) to generate word clouds.
- Option to enable/disable wordcloud during poll creation.
- Settings configuration to enable/disable use of public Internet for access to Quickchart.
- If public Internet access not granted, insert response summary.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28918901/123744242-1b6d2d80-d8cc-11eb-8923-66fdc5e7b5bc.mp4

Closes #3
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 662944036, 'comment_body': "2 points here
1. If we're hard-coding this url here then how would the organisations who have hosted their own quickcharts server connect this app to it? For this reason, I'd earlier suggested to keep this api url as a app setting.

2. Are we planning to support paid plans for quickcharts? On the pricing page of quickcharts, it says that it has some rate limitation for the free plan - if that's the case then this might be an issue with bigger communities and for such big communities we'd need to add support for their paid plans.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 2, 11, 28, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663080400, 'comment_body': "Thanks Murtaza.
1. I realized (on contacting Ian from Quickchart) that they haven't integrated the word-cloud API in their [open-source](https://github.com/typpo/quickchart) codebase so there wouldn't be much use hosting a Quickchart server. The only way to access the word-cloud API is through the public URL which some organizations might not have access to. Hence the `boolean` app setting determining whether the org has access or not.
2. I'm unsure whether word-cloud hits would be included within the paid version since it hasn't been integrated. Moreover, the current rate-limitation is [1 chart/sec](https://quickchart.io/qr-code-api/) which I think should be pretty scalable.

Let me know your thoughts.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 2, 15, 6, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RonLek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663508172, 'comment_body': "1. If that's the case, then I think we don't have any option here with QuickChart :disappointed: Did he happen to mention when they will be allowing this feature? Also during your research did you find any alternative chart generator which provides on-premise hosting? I'm asking this because if we're introducing this public internet access limitation in this app, then the communities using Rocket.Chat within on-premise would miss out on this feature.
2. They say its a `60 requests per minute per IP rate limit` so if all the users are accessing the room from a different network then the limit is fair enough, however if all the users are on a private network behind a (Router + NAT) then although each of them will have a different local IP, but the same public IP - In that case if there is a single room with more than 60 users, they all would be identified as a single entity/IP and the rate limit will come into picture. Please give some thought on this and check if we can add support for the paid plan. Thanks.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 4, 13, 56, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 663681704, 'comment_body': "1. Unfortunately no. They seem to be in a fix whether to include it within the docker image or spin it out as a separate image. They don't seem to have time-boxed this change.
I found a few on RapidAPI but they don't seem to have a locally hosted or open-source version and are all paid.

2.  Valid point. I've mailed inquiring whether word-cloud is included within the paid plan. Will update here. Thanks.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 5, 6, 55, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RonLek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673220947, 'comment_body': 'We should always use app level logger i.e. `ILogger` interface for logging any errors in the app. All console logs gets logged on the server logs not on the app logs.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 18, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673223115, 'comment_body': 'Lets name it `wordCloud` to follow camelCase convention', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 20, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673223639, 'comment_body': 'Translations missing', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 21, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673223691, 'comment_body': 'Translations missing', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 21, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 673224927, 'comment_body': "There's a lot of tslint issues in this PR as well, please refer to my suggestion in previous PR for fixing it", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 20, 15, 22, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'murtaza98', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_body:

- Creates Poll Template Modal with `StaticSelectElement` to select poll template.
- Adds Overrated/Underrated Poll (Options: Overrated, Appropriately Rated, Never Tried, Underrated).
- Adds 1-to-5 Poll (Options: 1 - 5)
- Adds 1-to-10 Poll (Options: 1 - 10)
- Adds Agree/Disagree Poll (Options - Agree, Disagree)
- Adds Emoji Rank Poll (Options - ü§© Great, üôÇ Good, üòê Neutral, üôÅ Bad, üò¢ Awful)

pr_body:
- `/poll live <number>` subcommand based triggering for live polls added.
- Live Poll multi-question modal created to allow adding n number of polls.
- Time to vote (in seconds) provided within modal for user-defined poll end time.
- Live Poll specific optional properties added to `IPoll` interface to encourage code-reuse.
- Next Poll button added within Poll message for triggering next poll to be posted within the room.
- Updates Apps-Engine version to make use of [Scheduler API](https://developer.rocket.chat/apps-development/fundamentals-of-apps/scheduler-api).
- Adds "Poll will end <Time to vote>" block within live polls message.
- Registers and calls scheduler (`scheduleOnce`) to post next poll within room on Time to vote" expiry.

### Live Poll

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28918901/128911496-91b32a37-4495-4736-93fb-cb6daa9e14cf.mp4

### Live Poll - Late Retrieval

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28918901/129491137-5143f83c-b2f1-43d4-a078-a88130ded111.mp4


Closes #12
